<%
  set_seo_meta(
    title: "Privacy Policy - BizBlasts",
    description: "How BizBlasts collects, uses, shares, stores, and protects personal information.",
    canonical: "https://www.bizblasts.com/privacypolicy"
  )

  effective_date = "June 1, 2026"
  support_email  = ENV.fetch('SUPPORT_EMAIL', 'bizblaststeam@gmail.com')
%>

<%= render layout: 'shared/legal_page',
           locals: {
             eyebrow: 'Privacy Policy',
             title: 'Privacy Policy',
             summary: 'This Privacy Policy explains how BizBlasts collects, uses, discloses, and safeguards information when businesses and their personnel use our website, onboarding flow, dashboard, booking software, payment processing, and related services.',
             effective_date: effective_date,
             contact_email: support_email
           } do %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '1. Scope' } do %>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy applies to information we collect through
      <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-[0.95em] text-dark">bizblasts.com</code>,
      the BizBlasts application, custom-domain sites that we host for our customers, customer onboarding,
      account management, support interactions, and related services that help businesses operate online.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you provide your services to your own customers, leads, patients, clients, or other end users
      through BizBlasts, you are responsible for providing any notices and obtaining any consents required
      under the laws that apply to your business.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '2. Information We Collect' } do %>
    <p>We may collect the following categories of information:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>Account and contact data, such as name, email address, phone number, business name, and login credentials.</li>
      <li>Business profile data, such as business type, industry, service area, team members, services and products offered, branding, and onboarding responses.</li>
      <li>Customer data that you upload or that flows through your BizBlasts site &mdash; for example, the names, contact details, bookings, orders, and messages of the customers you serve.</li>
      <li>Communications and content, such as website copy, blog posts, product descriptions, support emails, SMS interactions, and any business memory or knowledge-base content you configure.</li>
      <li>Billing and transaction data, such as subscription plan, billing period, payment status, payout details, and customer identifiers generated by our payment processor.</li>
      <li>Usage and diagnostic data, such as log events, feature activity, browser or device data, IP address, session timestamps, and performance telemetry.</li>
      <li>Domain and infrastructure data, such as custom hostnames, DNS verification results, TLS certificate status, and deployment health for sites we host.</li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '3. How We Collect Information' } do %>
    <p>
      We collect information directly from you, automatically through your use of the service, and from
      service providers that support authentication, billing, hosting, communications, search, and
      infrastructure provisioning.
    </p>
    <p>
      For example, we receive information when you create an account, complete onboarding, purchase a
      subscription, take a booking or order through your BizBlasts site, send or receive SMS or email through
      a BizBlasts workflow, request a custom domain, or contact support.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '4. How We Use Information' } do %>
    <p>We use information as reasonably necessary to:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>Provide, maintain, secure, and improve the platform and related services.</li>
      <li>Create and administer accounts, subscriptions, dashboards, and tenant business workspaces.</li>
      <li>Operate booking, ordering, scheduling, payment, customer-management, and communication features for the businesses that use BizBlasts.</li>
      <li>Process payments, manage renewals, calculate platform fees, and send transactional notices.</li>
      <li>Provision custom domains, TLS certificates, hosting infrastructure, and email or SMS delivery.</li>
      <li>Respond to support requests, enforce our terms, investigate misuse, and comply with law.</li>
      <li>Send administrative, operational, security, and service-related communications.</li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '5. Legal Bases' } do %>
    <p>
      Where applicable, we process personal information based on one or more of the following grounds:
      performance of a contract, legitimate interests in operating and securing the service, compliance with
      legal obligations, and consent where consent is required.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '6. Roles: Controller and Processor' } do %>
    <p>
      For account, billing, and platform-operations data about BizBlasts customers and their personnel, we
      generally act as a controller of that information.
    </p>
    <p>
      For data about the customers, leads, and end users that your business uploads to or processes through
      your BizBlasts site (for example, your booking customers&rsquo; names, contact information, and order
      history), we generally act as a processor on your behalf. You remain the controller of that data and
      are responsible for the legal basis and notices required to collect and use it.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '7. How We Share Information' } do %>
    <p>We may disclose information to the following categories of recipients:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>Service providers that help us operate the platform, including hosting, database, authentication, search, communications, payment, email, analytics, image processing, and AI vendors.</li>
      <li>Infrastructure and deployment partners that provision custom domains, TLS certificates, and related systems.</li>
      <li>Professional advisors, auditors, insurers, and legal counsel where reasonably necessary.</li>
      <li>Government authorities or other third parties when required by law, legal process, or to protect rights, safety, and security.</li>
      <li>Parties involved in an actual or proposed merger, financing, acquisition, reorganization, or sale of assets.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Based on the current product architecture, these providers may include (and are not limited to):
      Stripe for billing and payment processing, Twilio for SMS, Resend or SendGrid for transactional email,
      Cloudflare for DNS, AWS S3 / CloudFront for asset hosting and delivery, Google for reviews and
      analytics, and AI vendors used to power optional content or assistant features.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '8. SMS and Calling Disclosures' } do %>
    <p>
      If you use SMS or calling features, you represent that you have the right to contact each recipient and
      that your campaigns, notifications, and conversational flows comply with applicable telecom, privacy,
      and marketing laws. Message frequency varies. Message and data rates may apply based on the
      recipient&rsquo;s carrier plan.
    </p>
    <p>
      Recipients may reply
      <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-[0.95em] text-dark">STOP</code>
      to opt out of SMS alerts and
      <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-[0.95em] text-dark">START</code>
      to re-subscribe where supported. Reply
      <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-[0.95em] text-dark">HELP</code>
      for assistance. Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '9. Cookies and Similar Technologies' } do %>
    <p>
      We and our service providers may use cookies, local storage, session technologies, and similar tools
      to keep users signed in, remember onboarding progress, secure the application, understand usage, and
      improve performance. You can manage many browser-level controls through your device or browser
      settings, and you can adjust your preferences using the &ldquo;Consent Preferences&rdquo; link in the
      site footer.
    </p>
    <p>
      For more detail, see our
      <%= link_to 'Cookies Policy', '/cookies', class: 'text-primary hover:underline' %>.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '10. Data Retention' } do %>
    <p>
      We retain personal information for as long as reasonably necessary to provide the service, comply with
      legal obligations, resolve disputes, enforce agreements, maintain security, and support legitimate
      business needs. Retention periods vary by data type, sensitivity, operational need, and legal
      requirements. When your account closes, we may retain anonymized or aggregated data for analytics and
      product improvement.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '11. Security' } do %>
    <p>
      We use commercially reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards designed to
      protect information against unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration, including multi-tenant
      isolation, encrypted transport, and access controls. No system is completely secure, and we do not
      guarantee that information will always remain secure in every circumstance.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '12. International Processing' } do %>
    <p>
      Your information may be processed or stored in the United States and other jurisdictions where we or
      our service providers operate. Those jurisdictions may have data protection laws that differ from the
      laws where you reside.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '13. Your Rights and Choices' } do %>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live, you may have rights to request access to, correction of, deletion of, or
      portability of personal information, or to object to or limit certain processing. You may also be able
      to opt out of marketing communications while still receiving transactional or service messages.
    </p>
    <p>
      To submit a privacy request, email
      <%= mail_to support_email, support_email, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>.
      We may need to verify your identity before acting on a request. If you contacted a business directly
      through a BizBlasts-hosted site, we will generally route privacy requests about that business&rsquo;s
      customers to the business as the controller of that data.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '14. Children' } do %>
    <p>
      The service is intended for business use and not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly
      collect personal information directly from children under 13 through the service. Individual businesses
      that use BizBlasts are responsible for their own compliance with child-directed-services laws (such as
      COPPA) where applicable.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '15. Changes to This Policy' } do %>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we may post the
      revised version on the site, update the effective date above, and take additional steps if required by
      law.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '16. Contact Us' } do %>
    <p>
      Questions, requests, or concerns about this Privacy Policy may be sent to
      <%= mail_to support_email, support_email, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>.
    </p>
  <% end %>

<% end %>
